        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl leading-snug">Why $275 Is Mid-Market</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-4 text-navy-soft leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Ghostwriters with bestseller credits typically work flat-fee at $100,000&ndash;$300,000 per
          book&mdash;an effective $300&ndash;$500 per hour when honestly accounted, and often higher with
          revisions. Publishing houses pricing senior collaborators internally land in the same range.
        </p>
        <p>
          $275/hr for a writer with a Lionsgate feature, a Simon &amp; Schuster trilogy, FranklinCovey
          credits, and Grey + Miller representation is a mid-market rate with two practical advantages:
          <strong class="text-navy font-semibold">transparency</strong>
          (you pay only for what the manuscript actually requires) and
          <strong class="text-navy font-semibold">scope flexibility</strong>
          (architecture-only, chapter rescue, or full ghostwrite&mdash;priced honestly).
        </p>
      </div>
